title:  "Network File Server | C++"
layout: post
---

I developed a multi-threaded network file server that provides a hierarchical file system using fine-grained locking, socket programming, client-server systems, and network protocols.

Created a multi-threaded network file server providing a hierarchical file system with communication over TCP sockets

Reduced average server latency by 38% by caching a list of free disk blocks between requests, utilizing Boost upgradable reader-writer locks for more concurrent disk access, and hand-over-hand locking when traversing file system